<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-step-by-step-instructions"><span class="ez-toc-section" id="Step_By_Step_Instructions"></span>Step By Step Instructions<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span></h2>



<div class="wp-block-group has-base-alt-background-color has-background has-global-padding is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-group-is-layout-71f8e6ab wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained" style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);line-height:1.6">
<div class="wp-block-group is-content-justification-center is-nowrap is-layout-flex wp-container-core-group-is-layout-23441af8 wp-block-group-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-group is-square has-secondary-background-color has-background has-global-padding is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained" style="border-radius:9999px">
<p class="has-base-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-5f04e94359fb99f61e6d4f225a354995" style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30)">1</p>
</div>
</div>



<p class="has-text-align-center has-secondary-dark-color has-text-color has-link-color has-secondary-font-family has-x-large-font-size wp-elements-d29d33805d1b19bb89dc294babc2621a" style="margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--20);line-height:1.1"><strong>Make the Dough</strong></p>



<p>Whisk the warm milk and sugar together, then sprinkle the yeast over the top. Let it sit until foamy. Add the egg and melted butter, then mix in the salt and 3 cups of flour. Stir until a shaggy dough forms.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="683" src="https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-0-1024x683.jpg" alt="Two photos of a metal mixing bowl with a foamy, bubbly yeast mixture inside&mdash;a key step in making Cinnamon Crumb Buns. The left image shows a top-down view, while the right is a close-up of the foamy yeast surface." class="wp-image-82537" srcset="https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-0-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-0-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-0-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-0.jpg 1200w" sizes="auto" data-pin-media="https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-0.jpg" fetchpriority="low"></figure>
</div>



<div class="wp-block-group has-base-alt-background-color has-background has-global-padding is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-group-is-layout-71f8e6ab wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained" style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);line-height:1.6">
<div class="wp-block-group is-content-justification-center is-nowrap is-layout-flex wp-container-core-group-is-layout-23441af8 wp-block-group-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-group is-square has-secondary-background-color has-background has-global-padding is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained" style="border-radius:9999px">
<p class="has-base-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-25606a12efafa2fd0597b60acd9dc5ae" style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30)">2</p>
</div>
</div>



<p class="has-text-align-center has-secondary-dark-color has-text-color has-link-color has-secondary-font-family has-x-large-font-size wp-elements-2b23311f8f860d07b30155ce235a2d4b" style="margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--20);line-height:1.1"><strong>Knead and Rise</strong></p>



<p>Knead the dough for 6 to 8 minutes until smooth and slightly tacky. If it sticks heavily, add a little more flour. Place it in a greased bowl, cover, and let it rise until doubled. It should look puffy and airy when ready.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="683" src="https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-1-1-1024x683.jpg" alt="Two glass bowls with dough for Cinnamon Crumb Buns: the left bowl holds a small ball of dough before rising, while the right shows the same dough, now doubled in size and covered with plastic wrap after rising." class="wp-image-82538" srcset="https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-1-1-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-1-1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-1-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-1-1.jpg 1200w" sizes="auto" data-pin-media="https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-1-1.jpg" fetchpriority="low"></figure>
</div>



<div class="wp-block-group has-base-alt-background-color has-background has-global-padding is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-group-is-layout-71f8e6ab wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained" style="content-visibility: auto;contain-intrinsic-size: auto 731px;padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);line-height:1.6">
<div class="wp-block-group is-content-justification-center is-nowrap is-layout-flex wp-container-core-group-is-layout-23441af8 wp-block-group-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-group is-square has-secondary-background-color has-background has-global-padding is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained" style="border-radius:9999px">
<p class="has-base-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-7a0aafe655f6c16f4920d1d30944ef34" style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30)">3</p>
</div>
</div>



<p class="has-text-align-center has-secondary-dark-color has-text-color has-link-color has-secondary-font-family has-x-large-font-size wp-elements-06b18319102ffc1598c703ddff24afe9" style="margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--20);line-height:1.1"><strong>Make <strong>Cinnamon</strong></strong> <strong>Filling</strong></p>



<p>Mix the filling ingredients until smooth and spreadable. For the crumb topping, combine the dry ingredients, then stir in melted butter until it forms large, soft clumps. It should resemble damp sand with chunks. Chill most of it, reserving about &frac12; cup for later.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="683" src="https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-2-1024x683.jpg" alt="Side-by-side images: on the left, a glass bowl with brown sugar, white sugar, butter, and spices for Cinnamon Crumb Buns; on the right, the same ingredients mixed into a rich, brown batter." class="wp-image-82539" srcset="https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-2-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-2-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-2.jpg 1200w" sizes="auto" data-pin-media="https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-2.jpg" fetchpriority="low"></figure>
</div>



<div class="wp-block-group has-base-alt-background-color has-background has-global-padding is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-group-is-layout-71f8e6ab wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained" style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);line-height:1.6">
<div class="wp-block-group is-content-justification-center is-nowrap is-layout-flex wp-container-core-group-is-layout-23441af8 wp-block-group-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-group is-square has-secondary-background-color has-background has-global-padding is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained" style="border-radius:9999px">
<p class="has-base-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-dc38cb0d2e1d2043e5b07d5ba9ead047" style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30)">4</p>
</div>
</div>



<p class="has-text-align-center has-secondary-dark-color has-text-color has-link-color has-secondary-font-family has-x-large-font-size wp-elements-db8ed6c8faea96c7b5b2a85c6353a223" style="margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--20);line-height:1.1"><strong>Make Crumb</strong></p>



<p>For the crumb topping, combine the dry ingredients, then stir in melted butter until it forms large, soft clumps. It should resemble damp sand with chunks.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="683" src="https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-1-13-1024x683.jpg" alt="A clear glass bowl filled with crumbly brown sugar and butter mixture, perfect for Cinnamon Crumb Buns, with a metal fork partially buried in the mixture, on a white background." class="wp-image-82587" srcset="https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-1-13-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-1-13-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-1-13-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-1-13.jpg 1200w" sizes="auto" data-pin-media="https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-1-13.jpg" fetchpriority="low"></figure>
</div>



<div class="wp-block-group has-base-alt-background-color has-background has-global-padding is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-group-is-layout-71f8e6ab wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained" style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);line-height:1.6">
<div class="wp-block-group is-content-justification-center is-nowrap is-layout-flex wp-container-core-group-is-layout-23441af8 wp-block-group-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-group is-square has-secondary-background-color has-background has-global-padding is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained" style="border-radius:9999px">
<p class="has-base-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-a6ad0d08472fdf6e6a80b3d91199e29b" style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30)">5</p>
</div>
</div>



<p class="has-text-align-center has-secondary-dark-color has-text-color has-link-color has-secondary-font-family has-x-large-font-size wp-elements-bdad72b25da704e694034bd0c835a054" style="margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--20);line-height:1.1"><strong>Assemble the Buns</strong></p>



<p>Roll the dough into a rectangle. Spread the cinnamon filling evenly, then sprinkle &frac12; crumb mixture over it.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="683" src="https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-6-1024x683.jpg" alt="A collage shows dough rolled out, a spoon spreading brown filling on dough, and dough covered with a crumbly brown sugar-cinnamon mixture&mdash;classic steps for making Cinnamon Crumb Buns, ready to bake." class="wp-image-82540" srcset="https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-6-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-6-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-6-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-6.jpg 1200w" sizes="auto" data-pin-media="https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-6.jpg" fetchpriority="low"></figure>
</div>



<div class="wp-block-group has-base-alt-background-color has-background has-global-padding is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-group-is-layout-71f8e6ab wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained" style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);line-height:1.6">
<div class="wp-block-group is-content-justification-center is-nowrap is-layout-flex wp-container-core-group-is-layout-23441af8 wp-block-group-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-group is-square has-secondary-background-color has-background has-global-padding is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained" style="border-radius:9999px">
<p class="has-base-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-015ec70e4b4cccd3799a32b001b65a30" style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30)">6</p>
</div>
</div>



<p class="has-text-align-center has-secondary-dark-color has-text-color has-link-color has-secondary-font-family has-x-large-font-size wp-elements-b278bf783d9bbfb82f156623a69ce50e" style="margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--20);line-height:1.1"><strong>Slice the buns</strong></p>



<p>Roll tightly into a log, seal the edge, and slice into large buns. Place them in a prepared baking dish. Cover and let the rolls rise for 30 to 45 minutes, until puffy and touching. Sprinkle the reserved crumb topping over the tops, then bake at 350&deg;F for 25 to 30 minutes, until the rolls are set and golden brown. Tent with foil halfway through if the crumbs start browning too quickly.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="683" src="https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-9-1024x683.jpg" alt="Four trays display Cinnamon Crumb Buns at every stage: covered raw dough, risen dough, topped with crumbly streusel, and fully baked golden brown buns. Each tray is lined with parchment paper." class="wp-image-82543" srcset="https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-9-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-9-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-9-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-9.jpg 1200w" sizes="auto" data-pin-media="https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-9.jpg" fetchpriority="low"></figure>
</div>



<div class="wp-block-group has-base-alt-background-color has-background has-global-padding is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-group-is-layout-71f8e6ab wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained" style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);line-height:1.6">
<div class="wp-block-group is-content-justification-center is-nowrap is-layout-flex wp-container-core-group-is-layout-23441af8 wp-block-group-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-group is-square has-secondary-background-color has-background has-global-padding is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained" style="border-radius:9999px">
<p class="has-base-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-28c0c4996072405afaa84b043013d6da" style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30)">7</p>
</div>
</div>



<p class="has-text-align-center has-secondary-dark-color has-text-color has-link-color has-secondary-font-family has-x-large-font-size wp-elements-81322227e851470d09d921a5c257e6a5" style="margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--20);line-height:1.1"><strong><strong>&nbsp;Ice and Serve</strong></strong></p>



<p>Beat the icing until smooth and pourable. Add milk gradually until it drizzles easily. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="683" src="https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-10-1024x683.jpg" alt="A glass bowl with cream cheese and powdered sugar, then mixed with a hand mixer, and finally smoothed with a spatula to form creamy frosting&mdash;perfect for topping freshly baked Cinnamon Crumb Buns." class="wp-image-82541" srcset="https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-10-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-10-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-10-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-10.jpg 1200w" sizes="auto" data-pin-media="https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-10.jpg" fetchpriority="low"></figure>
</div>



<div class="wp-block-group has-base-alt-background-color has-background has-global-padding is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-group-is-layout-71f8e6ab wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained" style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--50);line-height:1.6">
