<p class="has-base-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-425954b124263f007f7957f2895eeb67" style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--30)">8</p>
</div>
</div>



<p class="has-text-align-center has-secondary-dark-color has-text-color has-link-color has-secondary-font-family has-x-large-font-size wp-elements-d3ab911ce964277e95f76fb8ada272da" style="margin-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--20);line-height:1.1"><strong><strong>Serve</strong></strong></p>



<p>Spoon or drizzle over warm buns so it melts slightly into the crumb. Best served warm!</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="683" src="https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-1-33-1024x683.jpg" alt="Close-up of Cinnamon Crumb Buns with crumbly streusel topping and drizzled white icing, sitting on a baking tray. Plates are stacked in the background." class="wp-image-82542" srcset="https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-1-33-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-1-33-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-1-33-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-1-33.jpg 1200w" sizes="auto" data-pin-media="https://www.errenskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Cinnamon-Crumb-Buns-1-33.jpg" fetchpriority="low"></figure>
</div>



